    <node id="Parameters">
      <data key="d0">Parameters</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Parameters refer to the quantities that characterize distributions, mentioned concerning ordinary least squares and likelihood estimates in the lecture.&lt;SEP&gt;Parameters are values that define the characteristics of a model, often represented by theta in the context discussed.&lt;SEP&gt;Parameters are variables used in mathematical equations, expressed as phi one, phi two, up to phi K minus one, within the context of the discussion.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1dcfa4fdc2012c4e3a3c336e39e4afec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac0a1ea80eae7c222bf0ffd73875b023&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49f40563b7c8469bddeeb04d56b3cec7</data>
