    <node id="Exponential Family">
      <data key="d0">Exponential Family</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Exponential family is a class of probability distributions that includes the Parson distribution, governed by natural parameters.&lt;SEP&gt;The exponential family is a broader category of probability distributions that includes various forms like the Gaussian distribution as presented in the lecture.&lt;SEP&gt;The exponential family is a set of probability distributions that share a common form, allowing for convenient mathematical properties.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1dcfa4fdc2012c4e3a3c336e39e4afec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-674af09a64beddbff4e4e4b6e543709a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb276908b4dcc65a416b2c0490f93e3a</data>
