    <node id="Logistic Regression">
      <data key="d0">Logistic Regression</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Logistic regression is a statistical method used for binary classification problems, modeling the probability of an outcome as a function of one or more predictor variables.&lt;SEP&gt;Logistic regression is a statistical method for predicting binary outcomes based on one or more predictor variables.&lt;SEP&gt;Logistic regression is a statistical method discussed in the course for modeling binary outcome variables.&lt;SEP&gt;Logistic Regression is a statistical method used for binary classification problems, modeling the probability of a certain class.&lt;SEP&gt;Logistic regression is a statistical method for analyzing datasets in which there are one or more independent variables that determine an outcome measured with a binary response.&lt;SEP&gt;Logistic regression is a statistical method used for binary classification, discussed in the context of model parameters.&lt;SEP&gt;Logistic regression is a statistical method for predicting binary class labels.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-674af09a64beddbff4e4e4b6e543709a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d9737bbcc99dd55bb4b79cf055977a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa4c1f1bcccecc7faef4f12ad096763&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac0a1ea80eae7c222bf0ffd73875b023&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d65cfad802d1335db113217e2cb6afbe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38d7cccd02d2282bbd339ef51ba43f85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e92ae48716b56f03feed3a2648edf8bd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
