    <node id="Indicator Function">
      <data key="d0">Indicator Function</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The indicator function is a mathematical function that represents whether a condition is true, typically used in probability and statistics.&lt;SEP&gt;Indicator Function refers to a function that evaluates boolean statements and returns binary outcomes (one or zero).</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-674af09a64beddbff4e4e4b6e543709a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49f40563b7c8469bddeeb04d56b3cec7</data>
