    <node id="Newtons Method">
      <data key="d0">Newtons Method</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Newton’s Method is an algorithm used for fitting models, particularly noted for its speed when compared to gradient ascent.&lt;SEP&gt;Newton's Method is an algorithm known for its fast convergence properties used for optimization in machine learning problems.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7d9737bbcc99dd55bb4b79cf055977a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa4c1f1bcccecc7faef4f12ad096763</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767701766</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Gradient Ascent">
      <data key="d0">Gradient Ascent</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Gradient ascent is an optimization algorithm used to find the maximum of a function by iteratively moving in the direction of the steepest ascent.&lt;SEP&gt;Gradient Ascent is an optimization algorithm used to maximize a function by iteratively adjusting parameters.&lt;SEP&gt;Gradient ascent is a mathematical optimization method used to maximize a function, particularly in the context of maximizing likelihood.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7d9737bbcc99dd55bb4b79cf055977a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa4c1f1bcccecc7faef4f12ad096763&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac0a1ea80eae7c222bf0ffd73875b023</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767701767</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Theta">
      <data key="d0">Theta</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Theta represents a parameter value in the algorithms discussed, which is iteratively adjusted to minimize or maximize a function.&lt;SEP&gt;Theta is a parameter representing coefficients in the statistical equations used for modeling variable relationships.&lt;SEP&gt;Theta is a parameter that may be expressed as a function of phi in the context of the discussed probability distributions.&lt;SEP&gt;Theta represents a set of parameters in a statistical model that influences the calculations of likelihood and other formulas.&lt;SEP&gt;Theta represents parameters in statistical models, specifically in logistic regression, where it is optimized to maximize the log likelihood of the training set.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7d9737bbcc99dd55bb4b79cf055977a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac0a1ea80eae7c222bf0ffd73875b023&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb276908b4dcc65a416b2c0490f93e3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-023cc775f8b1adeebc9c45d2e9f6fe90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e92ae48716b56f03feed3a2648edf8bd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767701767</data>
