    <node id="Generalized Linear Models">
      <data key="d0">Generalized Linear Models</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Generalized linear models are a broad class of statistical models that extend linear regression models to allow for response variables that have distributions other than normal.&lt;SEP&gt;Generalized Linear Models are a class of models that generalize linear regression to allow for response variables that have error distribution models other than a normal distribution.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1aa4c1f1bcccecc7faef4f12ad096763&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38d7cccd02d2282bbd339ef51ba43f85</data>
