      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Generalized linear model refers to a flexible generalization of ordinary linear regression that allows for response variables with error distribution models other than normal.&lt;SEP&gt;Generalized linear models extend traditional linear models to allow for response variables that have error distribution models other than normal.</data>
