      <data key="d0">Sufficient Statistic</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Sufficient statistic is a statistic that provides as much information about a parameter of a statistical model as the complete data.&lt;SEP&gt;Sufficient statistic refers to a statistic that captures all necessary information from a sample to describe a particular probability distribution.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-38d7cccd02d2282bbd339ef51ba43f85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e92ae48716b56f03feed3a2648edf8bd</data>
