    <node id="Natural Parameter">
      <data key="d0">Natural Parameter</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Natural parameter is a function that helps define a probability distribution in the exponential family, influencing the shape and characteristics of the distribution.&lt;SEP&gt;The Natural Parameter in the context of exponential family distributions is a parameterization that simplifies the mathematical treatment of these distributions and is integral in defining the relationship between input features and the response variable in a GLM.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-38d7cccd02d2282bbd339ef51ba43f85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-486f08627d119b0879789e4cf88e8904</data>
